name: CNN
text:
New CDC guidelines address how schools can work with public health officials if an infected person has been on campus.

Rather than immediately shutting down, the guidelines say one option is an initial short-term class suspension & cancellation of events. https://t.co/2qSbVWKTTw

text: At least 26 cases of coronavirus in three states are being linked to the Sturgis Motorcycle Rally in South Dakota earlier this month https://t.co/QcNIxeyLrB

name: CNN
text:
RT @AC360: Researchers behind the influential IHME model are now projecting that the US coronavirus death toll could reach 310,000 by December.
 
“In some states…cases peaked and are coming down, but deaths haven’t,” IHME Director Dr. Chris Murray says. https://t.co/X4c8Z5weWo https://t.co/0FpwQwhoiA

name: CNN
text:
The coronavirus pandemic does not seem to be following a “wave-like pattern” like the 1918 flu pandemic, according to a WHO official.

“We don't think this is going to be a very seasonal virus,” professor of infectious diseases Dr. William Schaffner says. https://t.co/Kke6h239Vl https://t.co/5gJ8OXZOtB

text: Movie theater chains like AMC are reopening their doors with new safety measures and technology in place. CNN medical analyst @RWalensky weighs in on what moviegoers should consider before heading back in to see a film on the big screen. https://t.co/is3Rl3B4jQ https://t.co/nj8twby7Ei

name: CNN
text:
Parts of Iowa are still reeling from a powerful derecho. President Trump visited the state and pledged aid, but some say it’s not enough.

“He came by for what, for a picture, for a photo op? … No. I want to see boots on the ground,” one resident says. https://t.co/JkeHnKjjjj https://t.co/3PXy003GkV

text: “We have got to learn from the contested elections that we have had in this country,” says Charles Wells, former chief justice of the Florida Supreme Court during the 2000 election and recount, as President Trump continues to attack mail-in voting https://t.co/cnx3wPr7XA https://t.co/798TeJxHzi

text: The CDC has updated its school guidance. The update adds more details to existing guidelines that will better inform administrators' decisions about opening schools and limiting risk, according to CDC Director Dr. Robert Redfield. https://t.co/rYFYSoTs9d
